Consider a 3x3 matrix A that represents the sales of three different basketball products (Product X, Product Y, Product Z) in three different regions (Region 1, Region 2, Region 3). The entries of the matrix A represent the sales in thousands. 

Matrix A = 
[a, b, c;
d, e, f;
g, h, i]

You are given that matrix A is a nilpotent matrix of index 3, i.e., A^3 = 0, but A^2 ≠ 0. 

1. Prove that the determinant of matrix A is zero. 
2. Given that A^2 = 
[p, q, r;
s, t, u;
v, w, x], 
find the conditions on the entries a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i that make A a nilpotent matrix.
